.TH "lpfc_get_hba_info" 9 "lpfc_get_hba_info" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_get_hba_info \- Return various bits of informaton about the adapter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lpfc_get_hba_info
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *mxri "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *axri "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *mrpi "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *arpi "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *mvpi "  ","
.BI "uint32_t *avpi "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
pointer to the adapter structure.
.IP "mxri" 12
max xri count.
.IP "axri" 12
available xri count.
.IP "mrpi" 12
max rpi count.
.IP "arpi" 12
available rpi count.
.IP "mvpi" 12
max vpi count.
.IP "avpi" 12
available vpi count.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If an integer pointer for an count is not null then the value for the
count is returned.
.SH "RETURN"
zero on error
one for success
